Trivia[]

Rakan, the Charmer
  • Rakan and Xayah share unique interactions depending on the situation.
    • Both are the first voice-overs to feature ping-related voicelines.
  • His pick quote ▶️  "Let's dance!" is a reference to the eponymous song by David Bowie.
  • Xayah's pick quote ▶️  "I can never resist an invitation to dance" is an answer to Rakan's.
  • ▶️  "The only way to understand magic is to plunge into it, move with it, dance and dance!" is similar to the quote "The only way to make sense out of change is to plunge into it, move with it and join the dance" by the British speaker and mystic Alan Watts, whose teachings included philosophies similar to the ones observed in Rakan's script.
  • ▶️  "We are seen dancing and thought insane... by those who can't hear the music" references a famous quote by Friedrich Nietzsche.
  • ▶️  "When I get sad, I stop being sad and be awesome instead. True story" and ▶️  "Challenge accepted!" references Barney Stinson from How I Met Your Mother. The phrases have also reached meme status.[1][2]
  • ▶️  "I've been kicked around since I was born. It's alright! It's okay! I'm staying alive!" is a reference to the song Stayin' Alive by the Bee Gees.
  • ▶️  "Let's go! Baby! Baby? Baby? Baby!" may be a reference to a phrase from YouTube personality Markiplier's playthrough of P.T.[3]
  • ▶️  "Ha! I'm, G to the D! Golden Diamonds, boy! Woo!" is a reference to the song Crayon by G-Dragon.[4]
  • ▶️  "Name one genius that ain't crazy" is a reference to the song Feedback by Kanye West.
Star Guardian Rakan
  • ▶️  " Neeko, if you distract me with myself one more time..." refers to Neeko's champion trailer in which she mimics Rakan's appearance.[5]
